  "doc_id": "28425",
  "text": "Four out of the 10 screened imidazoles were detected: Dimetridazole, ronidazole, 5-chloto-1-methyl-4-nitroimidazole, and 5-nitrobenzimidazole. Ronidazole, 5-chloto-1-methyl-4 -nitroimidazole, and 5-nitrobenzimidazole had frequencies of detection of 100% in the ranges of 5.34-31 ng/L, 0.51-2.19 ng/L and 0.02-3.86 ng/L, respectively, indicating their widespread distribution. Ronidazole is an antimicrobial and anticoccidial drug and is mainly used for the prevention and treatment of histomoniasis and globidiosis in pets and wild birds [CITATION_1] . Imidazoles and their metabolites may cause cancer and induce organism mutations [CITATION_2] ; thus, their use is strictly controlled, and these compounds have not been reported in JZB or the surrounding sea areas.",
